The paper deals with decoding in channels with memory, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm proposed involves ranking noise sequences and subtracting them from the received signal, which is a computational task and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses error and success exponents, which are concepts in dynamical systems (cs.DS) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents worked examples and analyzes the complexity of the decoding scheme, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
